results.name: Triangle read by rows: T(n,k) = number of edges in graph whose vertices are forests with n unlabeled nodes and degree <= k and in which two vertices are joined by an edge if the forests differ (up to isomorphism) by exactly one edge.
comment: The number of nodes in this graph is given by A144215.
link: R. Neville, Graphs whose vertices are forests with bounded degree, Graph Theory Notes of New York, LIV (2008), 12-21.
